\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. C. edentula} (Bigelow) Hooker,{\i  Fl. Bor.-Amer.}{\b  1}: 59 (1830) ({\i C. americana} Nutt.). Plant up to 60 cm. Leaves subentire to pinnatisect. Pedicels 1·5-5(-8) mm in fruit. Petals 4·5-8 mm. Silicula 12-25 mm; lower segment flat at the apex, without lateral projections; upper segment 7-15 mm, 4(-8)-angled, tapered towards a flat base, without a membranous margin.{\i  Açores.} *Az. ({\i E. North America.})
